  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance in Shelter and Camp Management and Coordination for Affected Populations in Bujumbura Rural and Bujumbura Mairie</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve the living conditions of the displaced populations affected by the floods in the provinces of Bujumbura Rural and Bujumbura Mairie in Burundi through the provision of shelter and support in site management and coordination. As part of IOM&apos;s commitment to the application of the centrality of protection and to consider the risks of gender-based violence, cross-cutting activities will be conducted with a sensitive approach to the principles of protection, and inclusive of internally displaced persons, site managers and relevant actors.</narrative>
  </description>
